    "body":  "# MRL Increment 4: Expose Master Requirements List via API (Read-Only)\n\n## Objective\nExpose the Master Requirements List (MRL) through HTTP endpoints in the `IMQ.Api` layer using the existing `IMasterRequirementsReadService` from Core. This will validate the end-to-end read flow from Core ‚Üí API without introducing persistence, UI, or write logic.\n\n## Background\nThis is the fourth increment in the MRL implementation sequence:\n\n- **Increment 1**: Domain model (`QualificationRequirement`, enums)\n- **Increment 2**: In-memory service (`InMemoryQualificationRequirementService`)\n- **Increment 3**: Application-layer read service (`IMasterRequirementsReadService`)\n- **Increment 4**: Now exposing the MRL via API (this issue)\n\n\u003e MRL entries are represented by the `QualificationRequirement` entity introduced in Increment 1.\n\n## Scope (In)\n- Introduce a `MasterRequirementsController` (or similar) in `IMQ.Api`\n- Define the following read-only HTTP endpoints:\n  - `GET /api/mrl` ‚Üí Get all requirements\n  - `GET /api/mrl/by-type/{type}` ‚Üí Filter by `RequirementType`\n  - `GET /api/mrl/by-status/{status}` ‚Üí Filter by `RequirementApprovalStatus`\n- The controller should consume `IMasterRequirementsReadService`\n- Return domain objects directly (no DTOs at this stage)\n- Tests should validate routing and delegation behavior using mocked or in-memory read services. Full HTTP pipeline or serialization edge cases are out of scope. Full end-to-end integration testing is not required at this increment.\n\n## Scope (Out)\n- ‚ùå No authentication or authorization\n- ‚ùå No write methods (POST/PUT/PATCH/DELETE)\n- ‚ùå No database or persistence wiring\n- ‚ùå No frontend wiring or UI integration\n- ‚ùå No DTO mapping or transformation\n\n## Implementation Constraints\n- The controller must **delegate to** `IMasterRequirementsReadService`\n- No filtering or transformation logic in the controller itself\n- Controller methods must remain thin, testable, and declarative\n- Routes should follow standard RESTful conventions, lowercase and hyphenated if needed\n\n## Deliverables\n- `MasterRequirementsController.cs` (or equivalent) with GET methods only\n- Tests validating:\n  - Endpoints return expected HTTP responses\n  - Filtering routes call correct methods on the read service\n  - No service logic duplicated in controller\n- Ensure full compatibility with existing build and test infrastructure\n\n## Outcome\nAt the end of this increment, we will be able to query the in-memory MRL over HTTP with simple filters, completing the initial read-only architecture path from domain ‚Üí service ‚Üí API.\n\nThis prepares the foundation for future persistence, write logic, or UI consumption without committing to them now.",
